<paragraph blockId="123.[737,1329,289,716]" pageId="123" pageNumber="881">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1897" box="[739,998,289,322]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="123" pageNumber="881" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xanthinus">Lasiurus xanthinus</taxonomicName>
was previously considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="P. Gervais, 1856" box="[1059,1146,329,362]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="123" pageNumber="881" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ega">L. ega</taxonomicName>
, but studies based on allozymes and restriction-enzyme analysis of mtDNA suggested that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1897" box="[739,906,447,480]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="123" pageNumber="881" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xanthinus">L. xanthinus</taxonomicName>
should be treated as a distinct species. Recent molecular studies based on mtDNA and nDNA also recovered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1897" box="[738,907,565,598]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="123" pageNumber="881" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xanthinus">L. xanthinus</taxonomicName>
as a full species and placed it as the most basal lineage in the Yellow Bat group. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
